spans.text: wave Amid November's blast their naked arms , While their red leaves fall fluttering to their grave , And give again to dust May's vernal charms
the Muse's Son again I meet — I catch his notes amid the vulgar storm
the Muse the acts revive Which Time long past had veiled from mortal ken , Embattled squadrons rush , as when alive , And shadowy falchions gleam over shadowy men
the turf thy bloom will feed
which canopies the sons of breath
vulgar souls stoop to the fever's rage , Or slow , beneath pale atrophy depart
